    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><em>*As it turns out Euler’s identity was most likely discovered by an earlier mathematician, </em><strong>Rodger Coats</strong><em>, who died while Euler was still a boy. Don’t let this deceive though, Euler still had plenty of math to contribute to this and many other topics.</em></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
