    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The first step is just the definition of a Maclaurin series. The second step sets <em>eˣ </em>equal to <em>f(x)</em> and since <em>eˣ</em> is its own <em>n</em>th derivative (Lemma 3) we can plug <em>e</em>⁰ in for <em>f(0)</em>, <em>f’(0)</em>, <em>f’’(0)</em>, and so on to arrive at the third line. By simplifying <em>e</em>⁰ (which equals 1) we get:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
