0w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*JkPmdRLM31EcMmbIQ8EgVA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*JkPmdRLM31EcMmbIQ8EgVA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*JkPmdRLM31EcMmbIQ8EgVA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:974/1*JkPmdRLM31EcMmbIQ8EgVA.png 974w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:487/1*JkPmdRLM31EcMmbIQ8EgVA.png"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">While deriving this equation should hopefully be an enlightening exploration of the relationship between these three functions, the equation itself and its consequences are also of great importance in mathematics. I go into more detail on some applications of Euler’s formula (like complex exponentiation) in <a href="https://medium.com/@ozanerhansha/applications-of-eulers-formula-857bf60ba32d" target="_self">another post</a>.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7"><strong>**Side </strong>Note: Summation Notation</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">For all the infinite series discussed in this article, we used an ellipses, i.e. a …, to denote that they go on forever following the pattern. But this is a little hand-wavy, especially for a mathematician. Sure the patterns may look unambiguous, but consider the following numbers:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:28%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 227px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:454/format:webp/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 454w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 227px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*1RTuz2GBJAoaQZeP6YqxpQ.png 75